summary:
University Lecturer EU Law | PhD Researcher (LGBTQ+ Rights) | LinkedIn Trainer & Coach (Freelance) with a background in International and European law.

Author of ‘Europees recht begrepen’ (available at Boom here: https://www.boomdenhaag.nl/webshop/europees-recht-begrepen-1)

Currently the course coordinator and lecturer for European Union Law (2nd year Bachelor course) at the Erasmus School of Law. Previously the course coordinator for Public International Law (3rd year Bachelor course).

In addition, conducting PhD-research in the field of LGBTQ+ law (sexual orientation and gender identity law), specifically on equal marriage rights / same sex-marriage / gay marriage from a queer legal theory and comparative law perspective, but also interested in researching or lecturing on other topics of LGBTQ+ law, European Union law, International law and privacy law. I regularly give LGBTQ+ Law lectures for student associations and various academic courses.

Extensive experience in teaching, research and organizational responsibilities in various areas of law (for more information, see my profile below) and currently acting as a member of the Exam Commission, Programme Committee (Opleidingscommissie, OC) of the Bachelor in Dutch Law, member of the Diversity Platform at the Erasmus School of Law (https://www.eur.nl/esl/over/diversiteit-inclusie/people) and Bachelor Courses Coordinator within the Department of International & European Union Law.

Furthermore, because of my passion for social media, I have a company that provides social media advice and with it I regularly give LinkedIn (and other social media) workshops for bachelor and master students. I've given workshops at the Erasmus University Rotterdam, Hogeschool Rotterdam, University of Amsterdam, Vrije Universiteit, Leiden University, Hogeschool van Amsterdam and the University of Utrecht (in total, over 200 workshops).

For more information (such as teaching, lecturing and/or research opportunities, possibly giving a LinkedIn workshop, checking your LinkedIn-profile for feedback etc.), please do not hesitate to contact me by adding me on LinkedIn or sending me an email.

Specialized in: 
- Equal marriage rights;
- LinkedIn;
- European law (EU competition law; EU internal market law);
- International law;
- LGBTQ+ law;
- Sexual orientation and gender identity law;
- Artificial Intelligence;
- (The use of) social media;
- Tech stuff;
- Coaching & Training;
- Constitutional law; 
- Administrative law; 
- Privacy law;
- Anti-Terrorism law;
- Legal (Academic) Skills.

Also Proud volunteer at Rotterdam Pride.

profile_positions.description:
PhD: From a Queer Legal Theory perspective, how do courts deal with the sensitive topic of same-sex marriage? Part of my PhD:

- Received a Scholarship to attend and be part of the Human Rights Forum in Copenhagen, Denmark (‘Copenhagen 2021’), the largest LGBTQ+ rights related conference in the world;

- Presented during 'Gender in Law and Courts' Conference, European University Institute (EUI) and PluriCourts, Florence, Italy, Nov 2019;

- Published chapter: 'How do European courts approach the sensitive topic of same-sex marriage? An analysis of the case law of the ECtHR and the CJEU in the ‘Catch 22’-field of equal marriage rights', in W. Benedek, P. Czech, L. Heschl, K. Lukas & M. Nowak (Eds.), European Yearbook on Human Rights, Intersentia, Cambridge 2019;

- Published article: 'The right to same-sex marriage: Assessing the European Court of Human Rights’ consensus-based analysis in recent judgments concerning equal marriage rights', Dec 2017, Erasmus Law Review;

- Presented during the International Conference of Europeanists, Madrid, June 2019;

- Delivered guestlectures on LGBTQ+ Law for ELSA, ILSA The Hague, Erasmus Pride, the Mastercourse Human Rights in International Law (2020-currently) and the Minor Human Rights in a Pluralistic Society (2018-2021).

Acted as the Master Thesis Coordinator for the Department of International and European Union Law at the Erasmus University in Rotterdam.

- Helped students find suitable topics;
- Coordinated master thesis skill lectures;
- in coordination with supervisors, guided students through process of structuring their thesis and specifying their research questions;
- Facilitated and organised graduation ceremonies.
